HEADWORD: Top-chain
<hw>Top"-chain`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A chain for slinging the lower yards, in time of action, to prevent
their falling, if the ropes by which they are hung are shot
away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Top-cloth</ent>⟦br⟧
